{"title_page": "List of active separatist movements in Oceania", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{More citations needed|date=March 2008}}\n\nThis is a '''list of currently active [[Separatism|separatist]] movements in [[Oceania]]'''. Separatism includes [[autonomism]] and [[secession]]ism. What is and is not considered an autonomist or secessionist movement is sometimes contentious. Entries on this list must meet three criteria:\n#They are active movements with living, active members.\n#They are seeking greater autonomy or self-determination for a geographic region (as opposed to personal autonomy).\n#They are the citizen/peoples of the contested area.\n\nUnder each region listed is one or more of the following (except for The United States which only has the last one):\n*''De facto'' state: for regions with ''[[de facto]]'' autonomy from the government\n*Proposed state: proposed name for a seceding [[sovereign state]]\n*Proposed autonomous area: for movements toward greater [[Autonomous area|autonomy for an area]] but not outright secession\n**''De facto'' autonomous government: for governments with ''de facto'' autonomous control over a region\n**Government-in-exile: for a [[Government in exile|government based outside of the region in question]], with or without control\n**Political party (or parties): for [[Political party|political parties]] involved in a political system to push for autonomy or secession\n**Militant organisation(s): for armed organisations\n**Advocacy group(s): for [[Advocacy group|non-belligerent, non-politically participatory entities]]\n**[[Ethnic]]/[[ethno-religious]]/[[racial]]/[[Regionalism (politics)|regional]]/[[Religious denomination|religious]] group(s)\n\n==Australia==\n{{Main|Secession in Australia}}\n\n{{flag|Australia}}\n\n* Ethnic group: [[Indigenous Australians]]\n** Proposed state: Various\n** Pressure groups: [[Aboriginal Tent Embassy]], [[Murrawarri Republic]]\n\n[[Torres Strait Islands]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Torres Strait Islanders]]\n** Proposed state: [[Torres Strait Islands]]<ref>Sarah Elks (15 October 2011). [http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/indigenous/for-mabos-sake-let-my-island-home-go-torres-strait-elder-george-mye/story-fn9hm1pm-1226167158932 For Mabo's sake, let my island home go: Torres Strait elder George Mye]. ''The Australian''. News Limited. Retrieved on 25 April 2012.</ref><ref>Larine Statham (17 October 2011). [http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/progress-for-torres-strait-independence/story-fn6ck2c6-1226168521353 Progress for Torres Strait independence]. ''Courier Mail''. Queensland Newspapers. Retrieved on 25 April 2012.</ref><ref>(5 August 2009). [http://www.news.com.au/breaking-news/mp-supports-torres-strait-independence/story-e6frfku0-1225758260046 MP supports Torres Strait independence]. news.com.au. News Limited. Retrieved on 25 April 2012.</ref>\n{{flag|Norfolk Island}}\n* Ethnic group: [[Norfolk Islanders]]\n**Proposed state: [[Politics of Norfolk Island#Independence|Norfolk Island]]\n{{flag|Western Australia}}\n*Proposed state: [[Secessionism in Western Australia|Western Australia]]\n{{flag|Tasmania}}\n*Proposed state: [[Secessionism in Tasmania|Tasmania]]\n**Pressure group: [[First Party of Tasmania]]\n\n==Chile==\n{{Main|Secession in Chile}}\n\n*{{flag|Easter Island|name=Rapa Nui}} (Easter Island)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nativevillage.org/Archives/2004/Feb%204%20News/Native%20Village%20News%20,%20Feb%204%20,%202004,I%20127%20V1.htm |title=Native Village News |publisher=Nativevillage.org |date= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hectortobar.com/easterisland |title=easterisland - www |publisher=Hectortobar.com |date=2004-01-28 |access-date=2010-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406051611/http://www.hectortobar.com/easterisland |archive-date=2017-04-06 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n**Ethnic group: [[Rapa Nui people|Rapa Nui]]\n\n==France==\n{{Main|Secession in France}}\n\n*{{flag|French Polynesia}}\n** People: [[Tahitians]]\n*** Political party: [[Tavini Huiraatira]]\n\n* [[File:Flag of Moorea-Maiao.svg|23px|]] [[Moorea]]\n** People: [[Tahitians]]\n*** Proposed state: [[Republic of Hau Pakumoto]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geocurrents.info/geopolitics/the-republic-of-hau-pakumoto|title=The Republic of Hau Pakumoto?|work=GeoCurrents|accessdate=23 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|New Caledonia}}\n** Political party: [[Kanak Socialist National Liberation Front]] ([[Caledonian Union]], [[Party of Kanak Liberation]]), [[Kanak Socialist Liberation]], [[Labour Party (New Caledonia)|Labour Party]], [[Union of Pro-Independence Co-operation Committees]], [[Renewed Caledonian Union]]\n** Proposed state: [[New Caledonia]]\n\n==Federated States of Micronesia==\n{{Main|Secession in Federated States of Micronesia}}\n\n{{See also|2022 Chuukese independence referendum}}\n\n{{flag|Chuuk}}\n* People: [[Chuukese people|Chuukese]]\n** Proposed state: [[Republic of Chuuk]]\n<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.chuukstate.org/chuuk-independence-from-what-for-what/|title= Chuuk Independence\u2026From What, For What?|work=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n==Indonesia==\n{{Main|Secession in Indonesia}}\n\n{{See also|List of active separatist movements in Asia#Indonesia}}\n\n[[Maluku Islands|South Moluccas]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Moluccans]]\n**Proposed state: [[File:Flag of South Moluccas.svg|22x20px|border]] [[Republic of South Maluku|South Moluccas]]\n**Government-in-exile: [[Republik Maluku Selatan]] (member of the [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]])\n**Advocacy group: [[Maluku Sovereignty Front]]\n\n[[Sumba Island|Sumba]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Sumba people|Sumbanese]]\n**Proposed state: [[Sumba Island|Sumba]]\n**Advocacy group: [[Free Sumba]]\n\n[[West Papua (region)|West Papua]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Papuans]]\n**Proposed state: [[File:Morning Star flag.svg|22x20px|border]] [[Republic of West Papua]]\n**Militant organisation: [[Free Papua Movement]]\n\n[[Flores]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Flores#Culture|Floresian Catholics]]\n*Proposed state: [[File:Flore republic .jpg|20x20px|border]] [[Flores]]\n**Advocacy groups: [[Free Flores Movement]], [[Flores Youth Community]], [[Free Flores Organisation]]<ref>{{cite web|url= https://books.google.fi/books?id=pGClDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA505&lpg=PA505&dq=flores+merdeka&source=bl&ots=clB6QAI1DU&sig=ACfU3U1MYWOo6mhsFXHvSbFQl5slrKY-EA&hl=fi&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjfgejj997gAhVxp4sKHXQsAjYQ6AEwC3oECAQQAQ#v=onepage&q=flores%20merdeka&f=false |title=Encyclopedia of Stateless Nations: Ethnic and National Groups Around the World |work=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n==Kiribati==\n{{Main|Secession in Kiribati}}\n\n* [[File:Flag of Banaba.gif|20px|]] [[Banaba Island]]<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.banaban.com/\n|title=Banaba - Our Homeland\n|publisher=Abara Banaba\n|accessdate=2009-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==New Zealand==\n{{Main|Secession in New Zealand}}\n\n=== Autonomist movements ===\n\n{{flagicon image|Proposed New Zealand South Island flag.svg}} [[South Island]]\n{{Main|South Island nationalism}}\n**Proposed autonomous region: [[New Munster Province]]\n\n=== Secessionist movements ===\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of the Cook Islands.svg}} [[Cook Islands]]\n*Proposed state: {{flagicon image|Flag of Rarotonga 1858-1888.svg}} [[Republic of the Cook Islands]]\n**Initiative by the Cook Islands [[Ariki]] which considers both the [[Cook Islands]]' previous status as a British protectorate and its current status as associated state of [[New Zealand]] to be illegitimate. Aims to set up the Cook Islands as a sovereign state independent of both the [[United Kingdom]] and [[New Zealand]].<ref>http://www.sovereigncookislands.info/img/dummies/Mr%20Joe%20Legg%2003.pdf</ref>\n\n{{flagicon image|Tino Rangatiratanga Maori sovereignty movement flag.svg}} [[M\u0101ori people]]\n{{Main|M\u0101ori protest movement}}\n*Proposed state: [[New Zealand|Republic of New Zealand]]\n**Political parties: [[M\u0101ori Party]], [[Mana Party (New Zealand)|Mana Party]]\n\n{{