 Short Form Music Video]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Colin Thurston]]\n[[Category:Anime songs]]\n[[Category:1980 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Simon Le Bon]]\n[[Category:Songs written by John Taylor (bass guitarist)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Roger Taylor (Duran Duran drummer)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Andy Taylor (guitarist)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Nick Rhodes]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:replaced: Japanese language \u2192 Japanese-language", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Girls_on_Film"}
{"title_page": "Roberto Mancinelli (A&R)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n'''Roberto Mancinelli''' (born 12 June 1970 in [[Benevento]]) is an Italian [[Artists and repertoire|A&R]] executive, record producer and writer.\n\nThroughout his career, he worked with many Italian artists like [[Franco Battiato]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-488321/franco-battiato-firma-contratto-amministrazione-editoriale-sony-atv|title=\u221a Franco Battiato firma un contratto di amministrazione editoriale con Sony/Atv|first=Rockol.com|last=s.r.l.}}</ref> [[Gianna Nannini]], [[Vinicio Capossela]], [[Laura Pausini]], [[Irene Grandi]], [[Paolo Conte]], [[Mina (Italian singer)|Mina]], [[Adriano Celentano]], [[Premiata Forneria Marconi|PFM]], [[Nomadi]], and [[Nek]].\n[[File:Roberto Mancinelli.jpg|thumb]]\n== Early career ==\n\nBorn in [[Benevento]], Mancinelli grew up in [[Castelvenere]]. In 1988 he made his radio debut, working at Radio Telesia. A year later he moved to Bologna, where he attended {{ill|DAMS (University of Bologna)|it|DAMS|lt=DAMS}} at the [[University of Bologna]].<ref name=ottopagine>{{cite web|url=http://www.ottopagine.it/bn/daicomuni/4865/sanremo-nuovo-colpo-del-castelvenerese-mancinelli.shtml|title=Sanremo, nuovo colpo del castelvenerese Mancinelli|date=15 February 2015}}</ref> \nWhile a student, he worked as a DJ in some local venues and started collaborating with Punto Radio, Telemontecarlo and Videomusic.<ref name=ottopagine/> In 1991 he became music programming manager at [[Radio Kiss Kiss]] and moved to [[Napoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://corrieredelmezzogiorno.corriere.it/napoli/spettacoli/16_febbraio_03/napoli-015-documentoqcorrieremezzogiorno-web-mezzogiorno-17efb400-caa1-11e5-b531-277d8572a1ed.shtml|title=L\u2019Italian Sound viaggia dal Sannio a New York, Mancinelli: \"La nostra nuova musica  \u00e8 nella Grande Mela\"}}</ref> In 1993 he moved back to Bologna, and the following year he started writing reviews for the music magazine ''Rockstar''.<ref name=ottopagine/>\n\n== A&R executive ==\n\n1995 saw his debut in the recording industry: he started working in the promotion department of Flying Records. In 1996 he became the A&R of CGD.<ref name=fiera>{{cite web|url=http://fiera.ge.it/en/37-news/695-roberto-mancinelli|title=FIM 2015 \u2013 Fiera di Genova|website=fiera.ge.it}}</ref> In 2000 he became A&R of S4 Records. In 2002 he founded another label, C&C Progetti Discografici.<ref name=fiera/> \nIn 2006, along with Fabio Canino, he wrote ''Raffabook'', dedicated to Italian singer, actress and television presenter [[Raffaella Carr\u00e0]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibs.it/raffabook-libro-fabio-canino-roberto-mancinelli/e/9788820041632|title=Raffabook \u2013 Fabio Canino \u2013 Roberto Mancinelli \u2013 - Libro \u2013 Sperling & Kupfer \u2013 I fuoriclasse \u2013 IBS|website=ibs.it}}</ref>\nSince 2007 he has been the A&R of [[Sony/ATV Music Publishing]] Italy. \nIn the following years he worked with [[Gianna Nannini]], [[Giovanni Caccamo]],<ref name=ottopagine/> [[Sonohra]], Karima, [[Nek]], [[Virginio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/spettacolo/2014/notizia/roberto-mancinelli-per-scrivere-una-bella-canzone-serve-l-urgenza-di-raccontarsi-_2052427.shtml|title=Roberto Mancinelli: \"Per scrivere una bella canzone? Serve l'urgenza di raccontarsi\" \u2013 Tgcom24|website=Tgcom24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://corriereinnovazione.corriere.it/2017/06/24/ponte-milano-new-york-la-musica-domani-b4165dea-58a1-11e7-bb8b-ea96e4db86e8.shtml|title=Un ponte tra Milano e New York per la musica di domani|date=28 June 2017|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref>\nIn 2014 he moved to New York City, where he acts as Consultant Italian Portfolio for Sony/Atv.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lavocedinewyork.com/arts/2016/03/16/alla-scoperta-roberto-mancinelli-sonyatv/|title=Alla scoperta di Roberto Mancinelli}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://italiany.us/roberto-mancinelli/|title=Italiany.us : Roberto Mancinelli}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://silvermusicradio.it/2015/04/27/roberto-mancinelli-il-discografico-della-sony-al-fim/|title=Roberto Mancinelli: il discografico della SonyAtv al FIM|date=27 April 2015}}</ref>\nIn 2015 he won the prestigious FIM Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://faremusic.it/2015/04/24/il-discografico-roberto-mancinelli-premiato-meritatamente-ai-fim-award-2015/|title=Il discografico Roberto Mancinelli premiato ai FIM AWARDS 2015|first=Mela|last=Giannini|date=24 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 he founded the record label I Mean Music & Management<ref>http://letsgodigging.it/2017/10/30/intervista-a-roberto-mancinelli-non-pensare-di-essere-credibile-se-racconti-storie-del-queens-o-del-bronx-e-va-bene-cosi-le-influenze-fanno-bene-lo-scimmiottare-cose-non-nostre-e-sempre-pericolo/</ref>. The first artist produced by the label is the young singer-songwriter Braschi, who took part at the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2017]] in the \"Nuove Proposte\" section, with the song \"Nel Mare Ci Sono I Coccodrilli\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iitaly.org/magazine/focus-in-italiano/fatti-e-storie/article/sanremo-2017-new-york-lanteprima-del-cantautore|title=Sanremo 2017: a New York l'anteprima del cantautore Braschi}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsimag.com/it/spettacoli/24164-la-conquista-dellamerica|title=La conquista dell\u2019America|first=Lorenzo|last=Mei|date=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2017 he joined [[Sugar Music]] Publishing's team, signing [[Alessandra Flora]] \u2013 one among the most prominent new songwriters in Italy whose songs appear on [[Gianni Morandi]], [[Raffaele Riefoli|Raf]], [[Malika Ayane]] and [[Nina Zilli]]<ref>http://www.rockol.it/news-680036/sugarmusic-contratto-alessandra-flora-imean-roberto-mancinelli</ref>.\n\n== Books ==\n* ''Raffabook'' (2006)\n\n== Awards ==\n* FIM Award (2015)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.robertomancinelli.com/}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mancinelli, Roberto}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:A&R people]]\n[[Category:Italian record producers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Benevento]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n'''Roberto Mancinelli''' (born 12 June 1970 in [[Benevento]]) is an Italian [[Artists and repertoire|A&R]] executive, record producer and writer.\n\nThroughout his career, he worked with many Italian artists like [[Franco Battiato]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-488321/franco-battiato-firma-contratto-amministrazione-editoriale-sony-atv|title=\u221a Franco Battiato firma un contratto di amministrazione editoriale con Sony/Atv|first=Rockol.com|last=s.r.l.}}</ref> [[Gianna Nannini]], [[Vinicio Capossela]], [[Laura Pausini]], [[Irene Grandi]], [[Paolo Conte]], [[Mina (Italian singer)|Mina]], [[Adriano Celentano]], [[Premiata Forneria Marconi|PFM]], [[Nomadi]], and [[Nek]].\n[[File:Roberto Mancinelli.jpg|thumb]]\n== Early career ==\n\nBorn in [[Benevento]], Mancinelli grew up in [[Castelvenere]]. In 1988 he made his radio debut, working at Radio Telesia. A year later he moved to Bologna, where he attended {{ill|DAMS (University of Bologna)|it|DAMS|lt=DAMS}} at the [[University of Bologna]].<ref name=ottopagine>{{cite web|url=http://www.ottopagine.it/bn/daicomuni/4865/sanremo-nuovo-colpo-del-castelvenerese-mancinelli.shtml|title=Sanremo, nuovo colpo del castelvenerese Mancinelli|date=15 February 2015}}</ref> \nWhile a student, he worked as a DJ in some local venues and started collaborating with Punto Radio, Telemontecarlo and Videomusic.<ref name=ottopagine/> In 1991 he became music programming manager at [[Radio Kiss Kiss]] and moved to [[Napoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://corrieredelmezzogiorno.corriere.it/napoli/spettacoli/16_febbraio_03/napoli-015-documentoqcorrieremezzogiorno-web-mezzogiorno-17efb400-caa1-11e5-b531-277d8572a1ed.shtml|title=L\u2019Italian Sound viaggia dal Sannio a New York, Mancinelli: \"La nostra nuova musica  \u00e8 nella Grande Mela\"}}</ref> In 1993 he moved back to Bologna, and the following year he started writing reviews for the music magazine ''Rockstar''.<ref name=ottopagine/>\n\n== A&R executive ==\n\n1995 saw his debut in the recording industry: he started working in the promotion department of Flying Records. In 1996 he became the A&R of CGD.<ref name=fiera>{{cite web|url=http://fiera.ge.it/en/37-news/695-roberto-mancinelli|title=FIM 2015 \u2013 Fiera di Genova|website=fiera.ge.it}}</ref> In 2000 he became A&R of S4 Records. In 2002 he founded another label, C&C Progetti Discografici.<ref name=fiera/> \nIn 2006, along with Fabio Canino, he wrote ''Raffabook'', dedicated to Italian singer, actress and television presenter [[Raffaella Carr\u00e0]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibs.it/raffabook-libro-fabio-canino-roberto-mancinelli/e/9788820041632|title=Raffabook \u2013 Fabio Canino \u2013 Roberto Mancinelli \u2013 - Libro \u2013 Sperling & Kupfer \u2013 I fuoriclasse \u2013 IBS|website=ibs.it}}</ref>\nSince 2007 he has been the A&R of [[Sony/ATV Music Publishing]] Italy. \nIn the following years he worked with [[Gianna Nannini]], [[Giovanni Caccamo]],<ref name=ottopagine/> [[Sonohra]], Karima, [[Nek]], [[Virginio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/spettacolo/2014/notizia/roberto-mancinelli-per-scrivere-una-bella-canzone-serve-l-urgenza-di-raccontarsi-_2052427.shtml|title=Roberto Mancinelli: \"Per scrivere una bella canzone? Serve l'urgenza di raccontarsi\" \u2013 Tgcom24|website=Tgcom24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://corriereinnovazione.corriere.it/2017/06/24/ponte-milano-new-york-la-musica-domani-b4165dea-58a1-11e7-bb8b-ea96e4db86e8.shtml|title=Un ponte tra Milano e New York per la musica di domani|date=28 June 2017|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref>\nIn 2014 he moved to New York City, where he acts as Consultant Italian Portfolio for Sony/Atv.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lavocedinewyork.com/arts/2016/03/16/alla-scoperta-roberto-mancinelli-sonyatv/|title=Alla scoperta di Roberto Mancinelli}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://italiany.us/roberto-mancinelli/|title=Italiany.us : Roberto Mancinelli}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://silvermusicradio.it/2015/04/27/roberto-mancinelli-il-discografico-della-sony-al-fim/|title=Roberto Mancinelli: il discografico della SonyAtv al FIM|date=27 April 2015}}</ref>\nIn 2015 he won the prestigious FIM Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://faremusic.it/2015/04/24/il-discografico-roberto-mancinelli-premiato-meritatamente-ai-fim-award-2015/|title=Il discografico Roberto Mancinelli premiato ai FIM AWARDS 2015|first=Mela|last=Giannini|date=24 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 he founded the record label I Mean Music & Management<ref>http://letsgodigging.it/2017/10/30/intervista-a-roberto-mancinelli-non-pensare-di-essere-credibile-se-racconti-storie-del-queens-o-del-bronx-e-va-bene-cosi-le-influenze-fanno-bene-lo-scimmiottare-cose-non-nostre-e-sempre-pericolo/</ref>. The first artist produced by the label is the young singer-songwriter Braschi, who took part at the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2017]] in the \"Nuove Proposte\" section, with the song \"Nel Mare Ci Sono I Coccodrilli\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iitaly.org/magazine/focus-in-italiano/fatti-e-storie/article/sanremo-2017-new-york-lanteprima-del-cantautore|title=Sanremo 2017: a New York l'anteprima del cantautore Braschi}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsimag.com/it/spettacoli/24164-la-conquista-dellamerica|title=La conquista dell\u2019America|first=Lorenzo|last=Mei|date=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn october 2017 he joined [[Sugar Music]] Publishing's team, signing [[Alessandra Flora]] \u2013 one among the most prominent new songwriters in Italy whose songs appear on [[Gianni Morandi]], [[Raffaele Riefoli|Raf]], [[Malika Ayane]] and [[Nina Zilli]]<ref>http://www.rockol.it/news-680036/sugarmusic-contratto-alessandra-flora-imean-roberto-mancinelli</ref>.\n\n== Books ==\n* ''Raffabook'' (2006)\n\n== Awards ==\n